devdoc.details: Library providing the following speed ups to an elliptic curve multiplication operation. - wNAF scalar representation - scalar decomposition through endomorphism

decomposeScalar(uint256,uint256,uint256).details: Decomposition of the scalar k in two scalars k1 and k2 with half bit-length, such that k=k1+k2*LAMBDA (mod n)

params._lambda: is a root of the characteristic polynomial of an endomorphism of the curve

decomposeScalar(uint256,uint256,uint256).return: k1 and k2  such that k=k1+k2*LAMBDA (mod n)

ecSimMul(int256[4],uint256[6],uint256,ui.details: Scalars k and l are expected to be decomposed such that k = k1 + k2 λ, and l = l1 + l2 λ, where λ is specific to the endomorphism of the curve.

params._points: An array with the affine coordinates of both P and Q, i.e., [P1, P2, Q1, Q2]
params._scalars: An array with the decomposition of k and l values, i.e., [k1, k2, l1, l2]

devdoc.title: Fast Elliptic Curve Multiplication Library

ecSimMul(int256[4],uint256[6],uint256,ui.notice: Simultaneous multiplication of the form kP + lQ.
